[B][SIZE=6]Default Placeholders:[/SIZE][/B]
[SIZE=4][B]%name%[/B] - Players name
[B]%displayname%[/B] - Players display name
[B]%prefix%[/B] - Players Prefix (requires Vault)
[B]%suffix%[/B] - Players Suffix (requires Vault)
[B]%uniquejoins%[/B] - Amount of players who have joined
[B]{#123456}[/B] - Hex color codes



[B][SIZE=6]How to use placeholders from[/SIZE][/B][/SIZE]
[SIZE=4][B][SIZE=6]CJM in other plugins:[/SIZE][/B][/SIZE]
[SIZE=4][SIZE=4]1. Install[URL='https://www.spigotmc.org/resources/placeholderapi.6245/'] [/URL][URL='https://www.spigotmc.org/resources/6245/']PlaceholderAPI[/URL].
2. Make sure the plugin you want to use CJM placeholders in supports PlaceholderAPI.
3. Use the placeholders!
